  1+  0728              ;                                       ****************************************
  2+  0728              ;                                       * TEXT BUFFER                          *
  3+  0728              ;                                       ****************************************
  4+  0728              ;
  5+  0728              ; LINE DIRECTORY: FLAT ARRAY AT DIRPAGE (#4000), IN A DEDICATED MAPPER SEGMENT
  6+  0728              ;   (DIRSEG). ALLOCATED AT STARTUP, BANKED INTO PAGE 1 VIA PUTP1, NEVER SWITCHED.
  7+  0728              ;   DIRECT ACCESS: ENTRY N IS AT DIRPAGE + N*3.
  8+  0728              ;   ENTRY LAYOUT: [1: SEG][2: WORD OFFSET WITHIN THAT TEXT SEGMENT]
  9+  0728              ;   CAPACITY: MAXLINES = 5460 ENTRIES (16384 / 3 = 5461, ROUNDED DOWN)
 10+  0728              ;
 11+  0728              ; TEXT SEGMENTS: ACCESSED VIA PAGE 2 WINDOW (TXPAGE = #8000).
 12+  0728              ;   PUTP2 TO SWITCH SEGMENT IN; COPY DATA; PUTP2 TO SWITCH NEXT AS NEEDED.
 13+  0728              ;   MULTIPLE SEGMENTS ALLOCATED AS FILE GROWS (ALLSEG).
 14+  0728              ;
 15+  0728              ; LINE RECORD (IN TEXT SEGMENT):
 16+  0728              ;   [1 BYTE : TEXT_LEN]   (0-80)
 17+  0728              ;   [N BYTES: TEXT]       RAW CHARS
 18+  0728              ;   [N BYTES: ATTR]       ONE ATTR BYTE PER CHAR
 19+  0728              ;   MAX: 1 + 80 + 80 = 161 BYTES (LINEREC)
 20+  0728
